    "chemicalDescription": [
      "sh-Polypeptide-90 is a single chain synthetic human peptide, produced by fermentation in  E. coli.2  The starting gene is a synthesized copy of the human gene which codes for Hyaluronan Synthase 2 used as such or adapted to the production host. It contains a maximum of 552 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation. The protein consists of the proper sequence of the 20 standard amino acids."
